    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-29T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-29T17:00:00-05:00" n="164"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d164">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119 P 43/917: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Special Representative</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HCEM1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">House</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-29T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 29, 1918—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>92. Following addition and corrections to list telegraphed in my 75 of November
                    26, 7 p.m.:</p>
                <p>Substitute <persName>H. A. [<hi rend="italic">A. H.</hi>] Lybyer</persName> for
                        <persName>W. S. Ferguson</persName> as assistant to specialists; <persName
                        corresp="#p_BWC1">William C. Bullitt</persName>, <persName>L. T.
                        Alverson</persName>, clerk, Mrs. <persName corresp="#p_AG1"
                        >Auchincloss</persName> and Mrs. <persName corresp="#p_BAWS1"
                        >Benson</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
